# 2026-04-08 12:46:55.281300
+We need to fix two critical orchestration flaws in the Nexus OS backend.
+
+Core Event Loss: Currently, DAG progression relies on Redis Pub/Sub (eventBus.subscribeGlobal), which drops messages if a worker restarts. Refactor the architecture to use BullMQ parent/child jobs or a durable Redis Stream for task_completed events to guarantee DAG progression.
+
+Wave Dispatch Transactions: In the orchestrator/missionPlanner, startDurableMission pushes tasks using a for loop with tasksQueue.add. If it crashes mid-loop, the DB is out of sync. Refactor this to use BullMQ's addBulk method to ensure all-or-nothing delivery of the task wave."

