# 2026-04-08 12:50:43.113035
+We need to fix a severe database bottleneck and an LLM cost leak.
+
+O(N^2) Database Pressure: In onTaskCompleted (or the equivalent task handler), the system is calling nexusStateStore.getMissionTasks(missionId), fetching the entire mission history. Refactor this and the corresponding DB queries to ONLY fetch the immediate dependents of the completed task.
+
+LLM Cost Leak: In agentRunner.ts, the state checkpoint is saved after the LLM returns. If the worker crashes during execution, the next worker wastes tokens re-running it. Implement a 'Pre-execution' lock/claim with a timestamp in the database right before runAgentWithCircuitBreaker (or the LLM call) so other workers know it is actively being processed.

